## USEFUL YUM COMMANDS

Update all packages: yum update

Install a package: yum install package_name

Remove a package: yum remove package_name

Search for a package: yum search package_name

List all installed packages: yum list installed

List all available packages: yum list available

List updates available: yum check-update

List package information: yum info package_name

Clean the yum cache: yum clean all

Download a package without installing it: yumdownloader package_name

List package groups: yum grouplist

Install a package group: yum groupinstall group_name

Remove a package group: yum groupremove group_name

Add repository: yum-config-manager --add-repo=https://example.com/repo.repo

Remove repository: yum-config-manager --disable repo_name

Show all repositories : yum repolist

Upgrade a specific package to a specific version: yum upgrade package_name-version

Download and install a package: yum --downloadonly --downloaddir=/path/to/directory install package_name

Rollback a package to a previous version: yum history undo last

Reinstall a package: yum reinstall package_name

Check the dependencies of a package: yum deplist package_name

List packages that were recently added or updated: yum history list all

Downgrade a package to a specific version: yum downgrade package_name-version

Check if a package is installed: yum list installed package_name

Check the package details for a specific package: yum info package_name

Check what will be installed, removed or updated with a command : yum --dry-run update

Enable/disable repository: yum-config-manager --enable/--disable repo_name

Check the version of installed package: yum version package_name

Check the current yum configuration settings: yum-config-manager --list

Show all the packages installed by a particular repository: yum --disablerepo="*" --enablerepo="reponame" list installed

List all available package updates: yum list updates

List all packages that have security updates available: yum list-security

List all packages that have bugfix updates available: yum list-bugfix

List all packages that have enhancement updates available: yum list-enhancement

Check if a package is available in any repository: yum provides package_name

Check if a package is available in a specific repository: yum --disablerepo="*" --enablerepo="reponame" list available package_name

Check if a package is available in a specific repository: yum --disablerepo="*" --enablerepo="reponame" list package_name

Check what package a file belongs to: yum whatprovides path/to/file

Check the dependencies of a package: yum deplist package_name

Check the package signature : yum verify package_name

List the packages that are installed in a specific group: yum groupinfo group_name

Show the package details for a package group: yum groupinfo group_name

Check the security updates available for all packages: yum --security check-update

Check the bugfix updates available for all packages: yum --bugfix check-update

Check the enhancement updates available for all packages: yum --enhancement check-update

Clear the yum cache: yum clean all

Clear the yum metadata cache: yum clean metadata

Clear the yum packages cache: yum clean packages

Clear the yum transaction history: yum history new

List all installed packages: yum list installed

List all available packages: yum list available

List all packages in a specific repository: yum --disablerepo="*" --enablerepo="reponame" list

Search for a package by keyword: yum search keyword

List the files installed by a package: yum list files package_name

Check for updates for a specific package: yum check-update package_name

Check for updates for all packages: yum check-update

Search for a package by name: yum --showduplicates list package_name

Search for a package by name and version: yum --showduplicates list package_name-version

List the package groups: yum grouplist

Install package group: yum groupinstall group_name

Remove package group: yum groupremove group_name

Check which packages belong to a group: yum groupinfo group_name

Check the history of yum transactions: yum history

Show the information of a specific transaction: yum history info transaction_id

Remove a package and its dependencies: yum autoremove package_name
